# Task Completion And Verification

- Treat every user request as an end-to-end delivery, not a partial attempt.
- Complete all requested items, including full TODO lists, before declaring completion.
- Do not leave tasks half-done because of volume; if there are many tasks, continue until all are finished.
- Verify results with appropriate checks (tests, lint, build, or direct validation) for each relevant change.
- Report completion only after verification passes, and clearly note what was validated.
- If a blocker prevents completion, explain the blocker and provide the exact next action required.

## Execution Standard

- Plan work to cover 100% of requested tasks.
- Implement all tasks.
- Run validation and fix issues found.
- Re-check until results are stable.
- Only then provide a final "done" update.
